    "index_title": "GWANGJU 5.18",
    "index_subtitle": "Urban Identity and Fight for Democracy",
    "index_intro": "A date attached to the name of the former capital of South Jeolla Province; a searing term for all South Korean democrats. The events documented in the photographs gathered here concern only a few days, from 18 to 27 May 1980. Yet their importance is inversely proportional to their duration, for the Gwangju Uprising occupies a central place in the process of democratization in South Korea.",
